  "prompt": "If I have a cold and drink juice straight from the bottle, and then when I'm healthy a few days later I drink from it again, can I get sick again?",
  "response": "Yes, you can potentially reinfect yourself or spread the cold to others by drinking directly from the bottle when you're sick. When you have a cold, viruses are present in your saliva and can remain on the mouth of the bottle. If you use the same bottle later, those viruses can still be present and may reinfect you or contaminate the bottle for others to use. To prevent this:\n\n1. Use a separate cup or glass when you're sick\n2. Wash the bottle thoroughly with soap and hot water\n3. Use disposable cups\n4. Avoid sharing drinks when you're sick\n\nIt's best to practice good hygiene to prevent spreading or reinfecting yourself with the same cold virus.",
